  "texts": [
    "Nonetheless, Jurado et al. (2015) state that there is no objective measure of uncertainty when it comes to assessing macroeconomic activity and uncertainty.",
    "To this end, the authors develop novel metrics of uncertainty and connect them to macroeconomic activity.",
    "The objective is to generate reasonable econometric estimates of uncertainty that are decoupled from the structure of specific theoretical models, as well as from reliance on any single or limited number of measurable economic indicators.",
    "Other measures of climate change policy uncertainty and overall economic policy uncertainty have emerged, with these indexes being built against the backdrop of newspapers using specific keywords, see Baker et al. (2016), among other.",
    "12 In the factor Stochastic Volatility model, Bayesian estimation improves on the univariate Stochastic Volatility implementations and offers multiple options to enhance efficiency (Andersen et al. 1999; Hosszejni and Kastner 2021)."
  ]
}